HEADWORD: Trypsinogen
<hw>Tryp*sin"o*gen</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Trypsin</ets> + <ets>-gen</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>The antecedent of trypsin, a substance which is contained in the
cells of the pancreas and gives rise to the trypsin.</def>⟦br⟧
